<br>
How the world will you say Mages have a strong defense.  We are defenseless, that is the point.  Mages have the least form of defense compared to any class.  <br>
<br>
No slow, root, (mez-summoned only), rune, fear, etc.  It seems to me the chain-casters are the only one against a root because it takes aways something they like to do.<br>
<br>
Also, btw Enchanters charm breaks...they root, mez, charm, have a rune...etc.  Pet dies we have????<br>
<br>
Necro pet dies they have fear, snare, FD.  You get the point?  <br>
<br>
Other classes have defense with or without pets, we are the only ones without.<br>
<br>
Reminds me of the excuses why Mages didnt need a Improved Invis before.<br>
<br>
Dont let your personal playing style keep you from speaking rationally.<br>
<br>
Immlazen <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=eandori>Eandori</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 531<br> <font color=#333333>(1/23/03 5:46:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=375.topic&index=185>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Root for Mages</span><hr size=1> Mage's defenseless?  Dude, our pets are the defense.  And they are damn good at it.<br>
