<br>
Defense?  More like speed bump in POP zones.  They last just long enough to GATE out.  Why should we have to gate to bind point?  <br>
<br>
Do you realize most classes with pets have defense besides there pets?  Why shouldnt a Mage?<br>
<br>
Example:<br>
Hunting in Tactics with a Druid.  His Charmed mob broke charm and was about to attack him,,,my pet hit him a few times while druid ran around until pet got agro.  My pet lasted 13 seconds.  The druid laughed recharmed his mob and said &quot;Mages pets are only good in groups&quot;.<br>
<br>
Sure in Old World are pets do provide defense,,,POP..Uhmm No!<br>
<br>
Now I think about it  WTF??  Why are Mages against getting things that would help the class?  That doesnt make any Freaking since.  Before POP some was against Nuke upgrades.  Some were against Pet upgrades.  No some are against Mages getting some type of defense other then hoping pet holds agro long enough so you can gate out,,because either you will run to the zone,,,or you will gate out in POP.<br>
<br>
Root would not make or break the Mages.  It probably would give us some our soloabilty back that we lost in POP.  But the ones that want to self destruct probably dont want to be able to solo either.  Its called Progression.  Hell, we couldnt mez or charm either, but we can now.  Myself they can take that and give me ROOT.<br>
