<br>
-You can still ghetto mez with root, that's VERY usefull in many situations.  <br>
-You can root a running mob to stop him from aggroing others.  <br>
-You can root a mob then cast non-root breaking spells to build aggro and prepare to aggro kite.<br>
-You can root a mob and blind/fear/debuff etc then break and start the fight.<br>
-You can root a mob to make him hit the closest target.<br>
-You can root a mob to aid in pulling singles or at the very least less then without root.<br>
-You can use root to split mobs on pull.<br>
-You can use root as a defense while your getting beat on with no pet up.  Root mob, back up.<br>
<br>
Root has ALOT of uses other then trivializing chained pets.  It's a game changing spell for a non-rooting class. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center">Master Eandori Raintree<br>
